NAME
    grep - search for patterns in input

SYNOPSIS
    grep [-i] [-v] <pattern>

DESCRIPTION
    Filters input lines matching a regular expression pattern.
    Reads from stdin and writes matching lines to stdout.

OPTIONS
    -i      Case-insensitive matching
    -v      Invert match (show non-matching lines)

EXAMPLES
    find . | grep users
        Find paths containing "users"

    ls -l | grep -i json
        Case-insensitive search for "json"

    cat file | grep -v test
        Show lines not containing "test"

    find . | grep "^/api"
        Regex: paths starting with /api

EXIT STATUS
    0       One or more matches found
    1       No matches found

SEE ALSO
    find, cat
